Step 0, Account

  • Make sure you have applied for a hiperGator account
    • https://caleb-huo.github.io/teaching/2019FALL/lectures/week1_overview/overview.html#(18)
  • If you do not have a hiperGator account, you will not be able to use anything in this slide.

Step 1, Network

  • If you are physically in UF, directly go to Step 2.
    • You are connected to the UF network
    • You are connected to UF eduroam
  • If you are out of the UF network, connect to UF VPN
    • https://connect.ufl.edu/it/wiki/Pages/glvpn-anyconnect-install.aspx

Step 2, login

  • https://ood.rc.ufl.edu/pun/sys/dashboard
  • After login, you will see the panel below

Step 3a, directories

  • Click on Files
  • Click on /ufrc/phc6068, you will see the panel below

Step 3b, directories

  • If your GatorLink userID is inside /ufrc/phc6068.
    • That will be your space to save data.
  • If your GatorLink userID is not inside /ufrc/phc6068.
    • Go to /ufrc/phc6068/share (highlighed by blue color)
    • Create your folder using your GatorLink userID.

Step 3c, directories

  • You can do basic file operations under your own working directory
    • New Dir
    • Upload
    • Download
    • etc

Alternative ways to transfer files: FileZilla Client

  • Download:
    • https://filezilla-project.org/download.php?type=client

Alternative ways to transfer files: FileZilla Client

  • Host: hpg.rc.ufl.edu
  • username:
  • password:
  • Port: 22
  • connect

You can transfer files between your local computer and hiperGator

Step 4a, Open Rstudio on HiperGator

  • Click on Interactive Apps
  • Click on Rstudio

Step 4b, Open Rstudio on HiperGator

  • Number of MPI Tasks (ntasks)
    • 1
  • Number of CPU cores requested per MPI task (cpus-per-task, -p)
    • 1 (suggested, unless you are doing parallel computing)
  • SLURM Account (account, -A)
    • phc6068
  • QoS (Required if custom Account is set, qos, -q)
    • phc6068
    • phc6068-b (use this option if all resources have been allocated)
  • Time Requested for this job (time, -t).
    • how many hours you want to allocate (be mindful as the whole class share 32 cores)
  • Maximum memory requested for this job (mem, -m) in GigaBytes
    • how much memory you want to allocate (be mindful as the whole class share 112Gb)
  • Others
    • Default

Step 4c, launch Rstudio

  • Click Launch Rstudio

Step 4d, working directory Rstudio

  • Check your current working directory
getwd()
  • Set working directory
setwd("Your working directory") ## can be created at step 3c

Step 5a, detach and resume Rstudio

  • Close the browser, your session is detached
  • By clicking the My interactive sessions button (See the red arrow below), you are able to resume your session.

Step 5b, close Rstudio session

  • Click the My interactive sessions button, and click the delete button

  • Or, close Rstudio (See red arrow in the figure below)
